modules.name: AWS.CloudSearch
modules.comments:
Amazon CloudSearch Configuration Service

You use the configuration service to create, configure, and manage search domains. Configuration service requests are submitted using the AWS Query protocol. AWS Query requests are HTTP or HTTPS requests submitted via HTTP GET or POST with a query parameter named Action.

The endpoint for configuration service requests is region-specific: cloudsearch.region.amazonaws.com. For example, cloudsearch.us-east-1.amazonaws.com. For a current list of supported regions and endpoints, see Regions and Endpoints.

declarations.comments: Creates a new search domain.
declarations.title: createDomain

declarations.comments: Configures an IndexField for the search domain. Used to create new fields and modify existing ones. If the field exists, the new configuration replaces the old one. You can configure a maximum of 200 index fields.
declarations.title: defineIndexField

declarations.comments: Configures a RankExpression for the search domain. Used to create new rank expressions and modify existing ones. If the expression exists, the new configuration replaces the old one. You can configure a maximum of 50 rank expressions.
declarations.title: defineRankExpression

declarations.comments: Permanently deletes a search domain and all of its data.
declarations.title: deleteDomain

declarations.comments: Removes an IndexField from the search domain.
declarations.title: deleteIndexField

declarations.comments: Removes a RankExpression from the search domain.
declarations.title: deleteRankExpression

declarations.comments: Gets the availability options configured for a domain. By default, shows the configuration with any pending changes. Set the Deployed option to true to show the active configuration and exclude pending changes. For more information, see Configuring Availability Options in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
declarations.title: describeAvailabilityOptions

declarations.comments: Gets the default search field configured for the search domain.
declarations.title: describeDefaultSearchField

declarations.comments: Gets information about the search domains owned by this account. Can be limited to specific domains. Shows all domains by default.
declarations.title: describeDomains

declarations.comments: Gets information about the index fields configured for the search domain. Can be limited to specific fields by name. Shows all fields by default.
declarations.title: describeIndexFields

declarations.comments: Gets the rank expressions configured for the search domain. Can be limited to specific rank expressions by name. Shows all rank expressions by default.
declarations.title: describeRankExpressions

declarations.comments: Gets information about the resource-based policies that control access to the domain's document and search services.
declarations.title: describeServiceAccessPolicies

declarations.comments: Gets the stemming dictionary configured for the search domain.
declarations.title: describeStemmingOptions

declarations.comments: Gets the stopwords configured for the search domain.
declarations.title: describeStopwordOptions

declarations.comments: Gets the synonym dictionary configured for the search domain.
declarations.title: describeSynonymOptions

declarations.comments: Tells the search domain to start indexing its documents using the latest text processing options and IndexFields. This operation must be invoked to make options whose OptionStatus has OptionState of RequiresIndexDocuments visible in search results.
declarations.title: indexDocuments

declarations.comments: Configures the availability options for a domain. Enabling the Multi-AZ option expands an Amazon CloudSearch domain to an additional Availability Zone in the same Region to increase fault tolerance in the event of a service disruption. Changes to the Multi-AZ option can take about half an hour to become active. For more information, see Configuring Availability Options in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
declarations.title: updateAvailabilityOptions

declarations.comments: Configures the default search field for the search domain. The default search field is the text field that is searched when a search request does not specify which fields to search. By default, it is configured to include the contents of all of the domain's text fields.
declarations.title: updateDefaultSearchField

declarations.comments: Configures the policies that control access to the domain's document and search services. The maximum size of an access policy document is 100 KB.
declarations.title: updateServiceAccessPolicies

declarations.comments: Configures a stemming dictionary for the search domain. The stemming dictionary is used during indexing and when processing search requests. The maximum size of the stemming dictionary is 500 KB.
declarations.title: updateStemmingOptions

declarations.comments: Configures stopwords for the search domain. Stopwords are used during indexing and when processing search requests. The maximum size of the stopwords dictionary is 10 KB.
declarations.title: updateStopwordOptions

declarations.comments: Configures a synonym dictionary for the search domain. The synonym dictionary is used during indexing to configure mappings for terms that occur in text fields. The maximum size of the synonym dictionary is 100 KB.
declarations.title: updateSynonymOptions

declarations.comments: A PolicyDocument that specifies access policies for the search domain's services, and the current status of those policies.
declarations.title: AccessPoliciesStatus

declarations.comments: An Amazon Resource Name (ARN). See Identifiers for IAM Entities in Using AWS Identity and Access Management for more information.
declarations.title: Arn

declarations.comments: The status and configuration of the domain's availability options.
declarations.title: AvailabilityOptionsStatus

declarations.comments: An error occurred while processing the request.
declarations.title: BaseException

declarations.comments: A response message that contains the status of a newly created domain.
declarations.title: CreateDomainResponse

declarations.comments: The value of the DefaultSearchField configured for this search domain and its current status.
declarations.title: DefaultSearchFieldStatus

declarations.comments: A response message that contains the status of an updated index field.
declarations.title: DefineIndexFieldResponse

declarations.comments: A response message that contains the status of an updated RankExpression.
declarations.title: DefineRankExpressionResponse

declarations.comments: A response message that contains the status of a newly deleted domain, or no status if the domain has already been completely deleted.
declarations.title: DeleteDomainResponse

declarations.comments: A response message that contains the status of a deleted index field.
declarations.title: DeleteIndexFieldResponse

declarations.comments: A response message that contains the status of a deleted RankExpression.
declarations.title: DeleteRankExpressionResponse

declarations.comments: Container for the parameters to the DescribeAvailabilityOptions operation. Specifies the name of the domain you want to describe. To show the active configuration and exclude any pending changes, set the Deployed option to true.
declarations.title: DescribeAvailabilityOptionsRequest

declarations.comments: The result of a DescribeAvailabilityOptions request. Indicates whether or not the Multi-AZ option is enabled for the domain specified in the request.
declarations.title: DescribeAvailabilityOptionsResponse

declarations.comments: A response message that contains the default search field for a search domain.
declarations.title: DescribeDefaultSearchFieldResponse

declarations.comments: A response message that contains the status of one or more domains.
declarations.title: DescribeDomainsResponse

declarations.comments: A response message that contains the index fields for a search domain.
declarations.title: DescribeIndexFieldsResponse

declarations.comments: A response message that contains the rank expressions for a search domain.
declarations.title: DescribeRankExpressionsResponse

declarations.comments: A response message that contains the access policies for a domain.
declarations.title: DescribeServiceAccessPoliciesResponse

declarations.comments: A response message that contains the stemming options for a search domain.
declarations.title: DescribeStemmingOptionsResponse

declarations.comments: A response message that contains the stopword options for a search domain.
declarations.title: DescribeStopwordOptionsResponse

declarations.comments: A response message that contains the synonym options for a search domain.
declarations.title: DescribeSynonymOptionsResponse

declarations.comments: The request was rejected because it attempted an operation which is not enabled.
declarations.title: DisabledOperationException

declarations.comments: An internally generated unique identifier for a domain.
declarations.title: DomainId

declarations.comments: A string that represents the name of a domain. Domain names must be unique across the domains owned by an account within an AWS region. Domain names must start with a letter or number and can contain the following characters: a-z (lowercase), 0-9, and - (hyphen). Uppercase letters and underscores are not allowed.
declarations.title: DomainName

declarations.comments: A list of domain names.
declarations.title: DomainNameList

declarations.comments: The current status of the search domain.
declarations.title: DomainStatus

declarations.comments: The current status of all of your search domains.
declarations.title: DomainStatusList

declarations.comments: A machine-parsable string error or warning code.
declarations.title: ErrorCode

declarations.comments: A human-readable string error or warning message.
declarations.title: ErrorMessage

declarations.comments: A string that represents the name of an index field. Field names must begin with a letter and can contain the following characters: a-z (lowercase), 0-9, and _ (underscore). Uppercase letters and hyphens are not allowed. The names "body", "docid", and "text_relevance" are reserved and cannot be specified as field or rank expression names.
declarations.title: FieldName

declarations.comments: The value of a field or source document attribute.
declarations.title: FieldValue

declarations.comments: The result of an IndexDocuments action.
declarations.title: IndexDocumentsResponse

declarations.comments: Defines a field in the index, including its name, type, and the source of its data. The IndexFieldType indicates which of the options will be present. It is invalid to specify options for a type other than the IndexFieldType.
declarations.title: IndexField

declarations.comments: The value of an IndexField and its current status.
declarations.title: IndexFieldStatus

declarations.comments: The type of IndexField.
declarations.title: IndexFieldType

declarations.comments: An internal error occurred while processing the request. If this problem persists, report an issue from the Service Health Dashboard.
declarations.title: InternalException

declarations.comments: The request was rejected because it specified an invalid type definition.
declarations.title: InvalidTypeException

declarations.comments: An IETF RFC 4646 language code. Only the primary language is considered. English (en) is currently the only supported language.
declarations.title: Language

declarations.comments: The request was rejected because a resource limit has already been met.
declarations.title: LimitExceededException

declarations.comments: Options that define a literal field in the search index.
declarations.title: LiteralOptions

declarations.comments: A named expression that can be evaluated at search time and used for ranking or thresholding in a search query.
declarations.title: NamedRankExpression

declarations.comments: The state of processing a change to an option.
declarations.title: OptionState

declarations.comments: The status of an option, including when it was last updated and whether it is actively in use for searches.
declarations.title: OptionStatus

declarations.comments:
An IAM access policy as described in The Access Policy Language in Using AWS Identity and Access Management. The maximum size of an access policy document is 100 KB.

Example: {"Statement": [{"Effect":"Allow", "Action": "*", "Resource": "arn:aws:cs:us-east-1:1234567890:search/movies", "Condition": { "IpAddress": { "aws:SourceIp": ["203.0.113.1/32"] } }}, {"Effect":"Allow", "Action": "*", "Resource": "arn:aws:cs:us-east-1:1234567890:documents/movies", "Condition": { "IpAddress": { "aws:SourceIp": ["203.0.113.1/32"] } }} ] }
declarations.title: PolicyDocument

declarations.comments: The current status of the rank expression.
declarations.title: RankExpression

declarations.comments: The value of a RankExpression and its current status.
declarations.title: RankExpressionStatus

declarations.comments: The request was rejected because it attempted to reference a resource that does not exist.
declarations.title: ResourceNotFoundException

declarations.comments: The endpoint to which service requests can be submitted, including the actual URL prefix for sending requests and the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) so the endpoint can be referenced in other API calls such as UpdateServiceAccessPolicies.
declarations.title: ServiceEndpoint

declarations.comments: The URL (including /version/pathPrefix) to which service requests can be submitted.
declarations.title: ServiceUrl

declarations.comments: Identifies the source data for an index field. An optional data transformation can be applied to the source data when populating the index field. By default, the value of the source attribute is copied to the index field.
declarations.title: SourceAttribute

declarations.comments: The source attribute name and an optional default value to use if a document doesn't have an attribute of that name.
declarations.title: SourceData

declarations.comments: Specifies how to map source attribute values to custom values when populating an IndexField.
declarations.title: SourceDataMap

declarations.comments: Specifies how to trim common words from the beginning of a field to enable title sorting by that field.
declarations.title: SourceDataTrimTitle

declarations.comments: The stemming options configured for this search domain and the current status of those options.
declarations.title: StemmingOptionsStatus

declarations.comments: Maps terms to their stems, serialized as a JSON document. The document has a single object with one property "stems" whose value is an object mapping terms to their stems. The maximum size of a stemming document is 500 KB. Example: { "stems": {"people": "person", "walking": "walk"} }
declarations.title: StemsDocument

declarations.comments: The stopword options configured for this search domain and the current status of those options.
declarations.title: StopwordOptionsStatus

declarations.comments: Lists stopwords serialized as a JSON document. The document has a single object with one property "stopwords" whose value is an array of strings. The maximum size of a stopwords document is 10 KB. Example: { "stopwords": ["a", "an", "the", "of"] }
declarations.title: StopwordsDocument

declarations.comments: The synonym options configured for this search domain and the current status of those options.
declarations.title: SynonymOptionsStatus

declarations.comments: Maps terms to their synonyms, serialized as a JSON document. The document has a single object with one property "synonyms" whose value is an object mapping terms to their synonyms. Each synonym is a simple string or an array of strings. The maximum size of a stopwords document is 100 KB. Example: { "synonyms": {"cat": ["feline", "kitten"], "puppy": "dog"} }
declarations.title: SynonymsDocument

declarations.comments: Options that define a text field in the search index.
declarations.title: TextOptions

declarations.comments: Options that define a uint field in the search index.
declarations.title: UIntOptions

declarations.comments: Container for the parameters to the UpdateAvailabilityOptions operation. Specifies the name of the domain you want to update and the Multi-AZ availability option.
declarations.title: UpdateAvailabilityOptionsRequest

declarations.comments: The result of a UpdateAvailabilityOptions request. Contains the status of the domain's availability options.
declarations.title: UpdateAvailabilityOptionsResponse

declarations.comments: A response message that contains the status of an updated default search field.
declarations.title: UpdateDefaultSearchFieldResponse

declarations.comments: A response message that contains the status of updated access policies.
declarations.title: UpdateServiceAccessPoliciesResponse

declarations.comments: A response message that contains the status of updated stemming options.
declarations.title: UpdateStemmingOptionsResponse

declarations.comments: A response message that contains the status of updated stopword options.
declarations.title: UpdateStopwordOptionsResponse

declarations.comments: A response message that contains the status of updated synonym options.
declarations.title: UpdateSynonymOptionsResponse
